<li>Among the regulators , GadE , a LuxR family regulator , serves as the central activator protein of AR genes such as gadA and gadBC ( 14 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Activation of this system initiates a transcriptional cascade of AR genes encoding regulators EvgA , YdeO , and GadE ( see Fig. 6 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21193607" target="_blank">21193607</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of the essential transcriptional activator of this system , GadE , is controlled by several regulators in a hierarchical fashion .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17660422" target="_blank">17660422</a>]<br></li>
<li>This system likely includes several regulons , which are under hierarchical control of a number of regulatory proteins : the two-component signal-transduction-system EvgA/EvgS , GadE , YdeO , GadX , GadW as well as the global regulators RpoS and H -- NS [ 18,19,22,23,35 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15313253" target="_blank">15313253</a>]<br></li>
<li>Components involved include a two-component signal-transduction-system ( EvgAS ) , three activators ( GadE , X , W ) , two sigma factors ( sigma S and sigma 70 ) , two global regulators ( Crp , H-NS ) and at least one regulatory loop ( GadX -- GadW ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12940989" target="_blank">12940989</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression and puriﬁcation of MBP-GadE , MBP-YdeO , and His6-EvgA fusion proteins .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15489450" target="_blank">15489450</a>]<br></li>
<li>Expression of these components is under the control of a complex network of transcription factors , including GadE , GadX , GadW , EvgA , YdeO , and H-NS [ 1 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=25375160" target="_blank">25375160</a>]<br></li>
<li>The possibility that the RcsB protein may interact with GadE Table 2 Quantitative RT-PCR analysis of genes related to RcsB phosphorylation in FB8 ( wild-type ) and BE1411 ( hns ) strains .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20435136" target="_blank">20435136</a>]<br></li>
<li>To identify targets of the RcsBeGadE complex that are involved in acid stress resistance , the mRNA level of genes previously identiﬁed as H-NS targets were compared between wild-type and hns , hns rcsB and hns gadE mutant strains using real-time quantitative RT-PCR ( Table 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20435136" target="_blank">20435136</a>]<br></li>
<li>This suggests that overexpression of either GadX or GadE alone , in an FB8 genetic background , is not sufﬁcient to induce expression of genes involved in the bacterial response to low pH when cells are grown at neutral pH. Overexpression of gadX signiﬁcantly induced the expression of 48 genes of the H-NS regulon ( Table 3a ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14702398" target="_blank">14702398</a>]<br></li>
<li>Chromosomal localization of genes involved in the low pH response Many genes identiﬁed by DNA array analysis ( Table 3 ) are regulated by both GadX and GadE .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14702398" target="_blank">14702398</a>]<br></li>
<li>GadE , is a regulator involved in the regulation of several 0002-6659 G 2004 SGM METHODS Bacterial strains , plasmids and growth conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14702398" target="_blank">14702398</a>]<br></li>
<li>To determine the impact of GadE in such pathways , we analysed the DNA-binding properties of GadE to the promoter region of several gene targets whose products are involved in each pathway .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=14702398" target="_blank">14702398</a>]<br></li>
